==English==
===Noun===
'''past historic tense'''

#(''grammar'') A [[tense]] used in some languages (such as French and Italian) in [[narrative]], and in spoken language primarily when reading narrative, for completed actions in the past or in speaking of the dead.

====Translations====
*French: [[passé simple]] ''m''
*Italian: [[passato remoto]] ''m''
*Japanese: [[単純過去]] (tanjun-kako; for French)、[[遠過去]] (en-kako; for Italian)

===Usage note===
In Southern Italy, the past historic is used more acceptably in spoken discourse.  
